conclusion¶

There are around 2000 unique movie generes there is is very hard to plot the data and the data is very cluttered. Therefore, the information would have been more clear if they have lesser categories.¶

There is positive correlation between revenue and budget as the budget in the movies increases the revenue also increases.¶

Looking on the release_year, there are more movies released in 2014 than any pther years.¶

The revenue has positive effect with the increase in the budget, vote_count, whereas increasing in pupularity¶

doesnot mean increase in revenue eventhough there are some few exceptions which shows higher revenue due to high popularity.¶

The revenue is highest when the runtime is around 200.¶

There are many outliers in the revenue_adj data.¶

The mean revenue is 3.982332e+07 whereas mean budget is 1.462570e+07.¶
